  "response": "Here are some tips to help you design effectively in Sketch:\n\n1. Learn the Interface\n- Familiarize yourself with the toolbar\n- Understand layers panel\n- Learn shortcuts\n- Get comfortable with artboards\n\n2. Basic Design Techniques\n- Create artboards for different screen sizes\n- Use symbols for repeatable elements\n- Utilize text and layer styles\n- Work with grids and layout guides\n- Use constraints for responsive design\n\n3. Design Workflow\n- Start with wireframes\n- Create basic layouts\n- Add colors and typography\n- Design UI components\n- Use libraries and shared styles\n\n4. Key Tools\n- Vector tools\n- Shape tools\n- Boolean operations\n- Mask tools\n- Alignment and distribution tools\n\n5. Advanced Features\n- Nested symbols\n- Smart layouts\n- Plugin integration\n- Export options\n- Prototyping\n\n6. Learning Resources\n- Sketch tutorials\n- YouTube channels\n- Online courses\n- Official Sketch documentation\n- Design community forums\n\n7. Practice Tips\n- Start with simple projects\n- Replicate existing designs\n- Experiment with different techniques\n- Keep learning and exploring\n\nRecommended plugins: Sketch Runner, Craft, InVision, Zeplin\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
